09-10 December - Blueberry Cake 

- 1 1/2 cup sifted flour
- 1/2   teaspoon salt
- 1/2   cup shortening
- 1/2   cup milk
- 1     teaspoon baking powder
- 2     eggs well beaten
- 1     cup sugar
- 1     teaspoon vanilla
- 1 1/2 cup blueberries

Sift flour, baking powder, and salt. Beat eggs and set aside. Cream shortening gradually adding sugar. Continue to cream. Add beaten eggs and blend until fluffy. Add 1/2 of the flour, mix stirring well. Add 1/2 of the milk to which the vanilla has been added. Add flour and milk until all used. Gently fold in blueberries which have been dusted with flour. Pour into a buttered 9" cake pan and bake in a preheated oven set at 375F for 30-40 minutes. Top of batter may be sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon before baking. 